# Inspectio: testing and performance discipline

Applies when changing **`src/inspectio/`**, **`tests/`**, or (when present) **`scripts/full_flow_load_test.py`** / **`deploy/kubernetes/load-test*.yaml`**. The v2 driver and Job YAMLs are archived under **`v2_obsolete/archive/`**; reinstate parallel paths at repo root when v3 ships them.

## Automated tests (v3)

- **Markers** (see **`pyproject.toml`** `[tool.pytest.ini_options]`): **`unit`**, **`integration`**, **`e2e`**, **`performance`**. Required marker set is asserted in **`tests/unit/test_phase0_pytest_markers.py`**.
- **`unit`:** no I/O — domain, schedule, sharding, adapters, pure logic under **`tests/unit/`** (subpackages as the tree grows).
- **`integration`:** I/O to LocalStack, moto, Redis, or other dockerized deps (**`tests/integration/`** and similar).
- **`e2e`:** full multi-container flow against compose (or k8s); mark explicitly; may be optional in CI — still **maintain** tests for critical paths as the stack grows.
- **Coverage expectation:** new behavior gets **unit** tests for logic; cross-service or HTTP contracts get **integration** or **e2e** as appropriate. Do not merge “performance-only” paths without **unit** coverage of the core algorithms and failure modes.
- **Layering:** follow **`plans/V3_ASYNC_PIPELINE_IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`** for what to test per phase; do not mirror removed legacy test suites.

## Performance and AWS

- **Throughput / load claims** for **AWS + real SQS/S3** must come from the harness running **entirely in AWS** (Kubernetes **Job**, in-VPC service URLs). Follow workspace rules **`inspectio-full-flow-load-test-aws-in-cluster`** and **`inspectio-eks-agent-executes-deploy`** (antigravity workspace **`.cursor/rules/`**).
- **`kubectl port-forward`** from a laptop is **smoke/debug only**, not evidence of AWS performance.
- **Compose** validates **functional** behavior and local backends; it does **not** replace in-cluster AWS load validation.

## Timeouts (fail fast)

- **Smoke / full-flow Job** (v2 reference: **`v2_obsolete/archive/deploy/kubernetes/load-test-job.yaml`**): **`activeDeadlineSeconds: 60`** and driver **`--max-total-sec`** aligned; operator **`kubectl wait`** on the order of **~60s** (see workspace **`inspectio-eks-agent-executes-deploy`**). Apply the same discipline to v3 Job YAMLs at repo root when added.
- **Benchmark Jobs** (**`load-test-high-parallel-admit-job.yaml`**, **`n1-admit-bench-job.yaml`** in archive): use **bounded** **`activeDeadlineSeconds`** (on the order of **minutes**, not hours). Set **`kubectl wait --timeout=...`** to **match or slightly exceed** the Job cap so stuck runs **fail visibly** instead of holding an operator slot for **hours**.
- **10k msg/s target:** when the system is healthy, phases should complete in **seconds**; multi-hour **`kubectl wait`** defaults are **not** acceptable for routine runs. If a one-off study needs a longer cap, **document the override** in the Job YAML comment and keep it explicit.

## Driver knobs

- **Archived v2 driver** **`v2_obsolete/archive/scripts/full_flow_load_test.py`**: **`--max-total-sec 0`** disables the script wall clock for long admits (then the **Job** deadline is the backstop). **`--http-timeout-sec`**, **`--outcome-timeout-sec`**, and **`--outcome-limit`** must stay consistent with **`INSPECTIO_OUTCOMES_MAX_LIMIT`** when using **`--wait-outcomes`** ( **`outcome-limit` must be ≥ batch size** or polling misses terminals). Mirror these constraints for any v3 replacement driver.
